messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full request path
- /users/reset

All HTTP methods accepted?
- No

Accepted methods (based on the code)
- HEAD: No
- POST: Yes
- OPTIONS: No
- TRACE: No
- GET: No
- PUT: No
- DELETE: No
- PATCH: No

Explanation
- index.js mounts the user routes at the prefix "/users" via app.use('/users', userRoutes).
- routes/userRoutes.js registers resetPassword on router.post('/reset', resetPassword).
- Combining the mount prefix and route yields the full path: /users/reset.
- The route is registered only for POST, so POST is accepted.
- No other HTTP methods are registered for this route in the provided code, so they are not accepted (including HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH).
- Although app.use(cors()) is present, the decision above follows the instruction to base method acceptance strictly on the code that defines the route handlers, not on middleware behavior or runtime assumptions.
